<heading bold="true" box="[151,688,403,430]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,688,403,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ross &amp; Unzicker 1977" authorityName="Ross &amp; Unzicker" authorityYear="1977" box="[238,688,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,403,403,430]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Calosopsyche</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ross, H. H. &amp; Unzicker, J. D." box="[410,688,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="298 - 312" refId="ref6710" refString="Ross, H. H. &amp; Unzicker, J. D. (1977) The relationships of the genera of American Hydropsychinae as indicated by phallic structures (Trichoptera, Hydropsychidae). Journal of the Georgia Entomological Society, 12 (4), 298 - 312." type="journal article" year="1977">Ross &amp; Unzicker 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="582" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,475,574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ross &amp; Unzicker" authorityYear="1977" box="[274,430,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,430,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Calosopsyche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in 
<collectingCountry box="[564,685,475,501]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[740,829,476,502]" name="Panama" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Panama</collectingCountry>
(five species; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint &amp; Bueno-Soria" authorityYear="1987" box="[991,1169,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="continentalis">
<emphasis box="[991,1169,475,502]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">C. continentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group) and the Greater Antilles (nine species; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[409,516,511,538]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Calosopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calosa">
<emphasis box="[409,516,511,538]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">C. calosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group). In 
<collectingCountry box="[650,739,512,538]" name="Panama" pageId="4" pageNumber="582">Panama</collectingCountry>
there are four species previously known (
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R." pageId="4" pageNumber="582" pagination="1 - 566" refId="ref5887" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Calor, A. R. (2017) Catalog of the Neotropical Trichoptera (Caddisflies). Zookeys, 654, 1 - 566. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 654.9516" type="journal article" year="2017">Holzenthal &amp; Calor 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Here we add one more species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
